      "date": "2020-01-22 15:14:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nThank you for the patch. This looks good. \n\nThere’s one case that we aren’t covering; when master (2.14) clients run testing with 2.11.0 servers. It would be good if we could cover this case. Maybe:\n\n[ \"$MDS1_VERSION\" -lt $(version_code 2.12.4) ] ||\n[ \"$MDS1_VERSION\" -eq $(version_code 2.11.0) ] &&\nskip \"Not supported before 2.12.4 and for 2.11.0\"",
